data.OTHER_INFORMATION: UNITED KINGDOM: England: Devon: North Devon: Matinhoe - West Woody Bay Wood. Cliff top 20m E of woodland edge above wring a peak. Group of 10 individuals seperate to woodland edge. West Woody bay Wood is dominated by Quercus petrea. Also present are Betula pubescens, Sorbus aucuparia , Ilex aquifolium, Ulex, and Corylus avellana Some Rhodedendron ponticum is present but it appears to be being controlled. The ground flora consisted mostly of Luzula sylvatica, Vaccinium myrtillus, and Fescues. No detailed survey was made of the woodland. The woodland is poorly fenced and I would imagine that it is grazed by the local feral goats and deer. There is a good cover of trees in South of the footpath in the steeper part of the coombe close to the waterfall (200m beyond the boundary of West Woody bay Wood shown on OS Map OL9). The west slope of the coombe below the coastal path is poorly vegetated scree. 51°13'42.6"N, 3°54'11.9"W. Female William Hinchliffe 18. 7 Nov 2011.
